# Git Commit Authorship

All git commits must be authored **only by the user**, never by Cursor or any AI agent.

## Required

- Use the user's git identity only: `Karar Tech <Haydar.AlKararLLC@gmail.com>`
- Commit messages must NOT include `Co-authored-by:` trailers
- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or similar
- Never list `cursoragent` as a committer or contributor

## When committing

```bash
# Correct
git commit -m "Your message" --author="Karar Tech <Haydar.AlKararLLC@gmail.com>"

# Wrong ¯ never do this
git commit -m "Your message

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>"
```

## When pushing profile or project repos

- Use normal `git push`, not force push on profile README repos unless explicitly requested
- Profile README repos (`username/username`) must keep GitHub's initial commit intact; add changes as new commits on top

## If Cursor still adds co-author trailers

Rewrite the commit object directly:

```bash
export GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="Karar Tech"
export GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="Haydar.AlKararLLC@gmail.com"
export GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Karar Tech"
export GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="Haydar.AlKararLLC@gmail.com"
TREE=$(git write-tree)
PARENT=$(git rev-parse HEAD^)
NEW=$(printf '%s\n' "Your subject" "" "Your body" | git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT")
git reset --hard "$NEW"
```
